at", "user_display": "Laywah", "version": "45.5.1"}, {"app_id": "mozilla-thunderbird.desktop", "date_created": 1484550856.0, "description": "Very good app to manage multiple email accounts. I also use it as my RSS/Atom feed app. Good and stable.", "distro": "Fedora", "karma_down": 0, "karma_up": 1, "locale": "en_US", "rating": 100, "reported": 0, "review_id": 1833, "score": 0, "summary": "Good email and RSS feed", "user_display": null, "version": "45.6.0"}, {"app_id": "mozilla-thunderbird.desktop", "date_created": 1489386017.0, "description": "Even though I use Evolution my self, there is no doubt in my mind that Thunderbird is one of the best ever created e-mail clients.", "distro": "Fedora", "karma_down": 0, "karma_up": 0, "locale": "en_US", "rating": 100, "reported": 0, "review_id": 2412, "score": 0, "summary": "The best e-mail client", "user_display": "Phoenix", "version": "45.7.0"}, {"app_id": "mozilla-thunderbird.desktop", "date_created": 1494252136.0, "description": "I've used almost every email client, but I keep coming back to Thunderbird. It's easy to use, customize and create macros for. My only problem is that is doesn't have a built in function for dealing with exchange servers.", "distro": "Fedora", "karma_down": 1, "karma_up": 2, "locale": "en_US", "rating": 80, "reported": 0, "review_id": 3116, "score": 0, "summary": "Almost perfect", "user_display": "William MacDonald", "version": "52.0"}, {"app_id": "mozilla-thunderbird.desktop", "date_created": 1494315870.0, "description": "Thunderbird is my primary email application. I use it with Enigmail for message signature and encryption and Lightning Calendar plugins. One feature that was removed and that I'm really missing is switching quickly between folder view (like all email, unread email, and unread email in compact view).\r\n\r\nThe address book management could be better and more modern standards compliant.\r\nThere are many plugins available to add missing functionality.\r\nI did not really evaluate any other email applications intensively. Sometimes I'm tempted to switch to Evolution because everything seems to be more smoothly integrated with my Fedora GNOME desktop. More tight integration with the LibreOffice application suite could be an improvement as well.", "distro": "Fedora", "karma_down": 0, "karma_up": 2, "locale": "en_US", "rating": 80, "reported": 0, "review_id": 3130, "score": 0, "summary": "Great email application", "user_display": "Jan Vlug", "version": "52.1.0"}, {"app_id": "mozilla-thunderbird.desktop", "date_created": 1503943788.0, "description": "Using Fedora 25. Cannot use Thunderbird now with this update. Waiting for next update. Til then, no Thunderbird!", "distro": "Fedora", "karma_down": 0, "karma_up": 0, "locale": "en_US", "rating": 20, "reported": 0, "review_id": 4469, "score": 0, "summary": "Version does not work, crashes all the time", "user_display": "Len Coop", "version": "52.2.1"}, {"app_id": "mozilla-thunderbird.desktop", "date_created": 1506754031.0, "description": "This is the best email client for Linux. It baffles me why anyone would use anything else.", "distro": "Fedora", "karma_down": 0, "karma_up": 0, "locale": "en_US", "rating": 100, "reported": 0, "review_id": 4848, "score": 0, "summary": "Superior to Evolution in every way", "user_display": "nuts", "version": "52.3.0"}, {"app_id": "mozilla-thunderbird.desktop", "date_created": 1509405178.0, "description": "I've been using TB for many years on Windows and Fedora and multiple accounts. I would never choose to use another email app.", "distro": "Fedora", "karma_down": 0, "karma_up": 0, "locale": "en_US", "rating": 100, "reported": 0, "review_id": 5226, "score": 0, "summary": "Full featured and dependable", "user_display": "Paul Varn", "version": "52.4.0"}, {"app_id": "mozilla-thunderbird.desktop", "date_created": 1510227336.0, "description": "Nearly Platform independent", "distro": "CentOS Linux", "karma_down": 0, "karma_up": 0, "locale": "en_US", "rating": 80, "reporte